transcript.text: Hi everyone welcome to onprint shop.
Today we will see when and how you can use a dependency rules like suppose you want to show, hide or replace any block value with the reference of another block value.
In this case you can use a dependency blocks like.

Let us understand the same in actual scenario like here if someone doesn't enter this direct number then you want to hide this D text and someone doesn't enter this cell number value you want to hide this C text.
And the same you want to achieve for this 3 remaining block as well.
So when you have such a requirement you can use a dependency rules like here you can select dependency rules then add the new rule gave the rule name status to enable or disable this rule.
And this type would be applicable when you have multiple IF conditions like if you want to allow the system to perform this action plan only when all this IF condition would fulfill.
In this requirement you can select and type and if you want to allow the system to perform this action plan only any of any of one if condition with fulfill then you can use or type.
As of now we have only one condition like if someone doesn't enter e-mail.

If e-mail is empty then we want to hide this etext and then again if someone doesn't enter the direct number direct number then we want to if direct number is empty then we want to hide this D value and the same if cell number is empty then hide C And the same I have done for this fax and mobile number as well.
So now let us see the result like here.
If I don't enter this direct number system would hide this DTXT.
The same if I don't enter the cell number system would hide the C.
And now how to move this blog based on with the reference of another blog that we will we will see in our next video.
Like how you can use the alignment rules like the same way you can show or hide a certain blogs as well like here in this template.
Based on this drop down value we want to change this block value as well.
Like if someone select the burger, when customer will get the burger, you want to change this message if someone select the meal then when customer will get the meal and if someone select the coke.
Like this offer will not be applicable on public holidays so we can show this message as well and but this offer would be applicable for burger in all the public holidays.
So to achieve these same here what I did is like here this drop down block name is offer.
So if offer is equal to free burger, if someone select the burger from that drop down value then set value.
This block name is purchase.
So purchase set value with the purchase of will ferry and large drink.
And for second terms like if someone select this free meal from this drop down then we want to set the grib of free yummy.
So here if offer value free meal then set value on which block we want to set this value that we need to select here like purchase and value which value we want to set.
Like to show or hide certain blocks like if offer is equal to flat 30% then set value purchase and show this valid offer Like this blog name is valid.
So we want to show this message only when someone select the free coke else that would be hide.
So that's it.
This is how you can create dependency block.
Let us know if you have any feedback query while creating dependency block we would be more than happy to assist you.
Bye bye.
